reviews.review_text: Great Show! This is another one of those justifiably famous shows of summer '89.  Lots of energy, great sound, great crowd.  Bobby, Brent and Phil all had strong nights vocally, Jerry was solid.  "Let the good Times Roll" sets the mood right out of the gate, Box o R a strong end to the 1st set, and Foolish Heart as a rare encore (I am pretty sure at least) give this show a unique, memorable flavor.  Well worth adding to your collection.
